  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_10' aria-label=\" Renuka versus State of Karnataka and Anr. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('10','2025','2025_4_1936_1942','2025INSC596'); ><font size='4'> <strong>RENUKA<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF KARNATAKA AND ANR. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 4 S.C.R. 1936</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 596</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010005482025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : PAMIDIGHANTAM SRI NARASIMHA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, JOYMALYA BAGCHI</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Appellant-wife has challenged the impugned order whereby the High Court quashed proceeding u/ss.498-A, 324, 355, 504, 506 r/w. s.149 of the Penal Code, 1860 against the respondent-husband. Headnotes&dagger; Penal Code, 1860 &ndash; ss.498-A, 324, 355, 504, 506 r/w. s.149 and other in-laws harassed appellant-wife physically and mentally and also demanded dowry &ndash; Appellant started residing at her parental home &ndash; On 27.10.2020, respondent-husband and other in-laws went to parental home of appellant and threw chilli powder in her eyes, abused<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 29-04-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 2309/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('10','2025','2025_4_1936_1942','2025INSC596','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'